CRITICAL RULE — INSPECTION DEADLINE COSTS TIME:
The incoming container must reach its target slot within a fixed inspection window — customs inspectors are waiting at the slot and the inspection report can only be filed if the container is in place before the window expires. Every character sent on the link channel costs one second of the round's remaining inspection window. If the total communication time (from ALL messages by all three of you) exceeds the round's window, the inspection slot is missed and the round fails — the container is not placed and no inspection happens.
